The paper discusses algorithms for understanding natural language user instructions for service robots, which involves processing high-level instructions and generating low-level task plans. This falls under the intersection of several sub-fields in computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), robotics (cs.RO), natural language processing (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), and software engineering (cs.SD). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories for this paper.
